## 2. Security

### ✅ DONE — Session Security
- HMAC-SHA256 signed cookies (tamper-proof)
- Constant-time comparison (no timing attacks)
- HTTP-only, secure, SameSite cookies

### ✅ DONE — Input Validation
- Zod schema validation on analyze payload
- Rate limiting on OTP (3 per 10 min)
- Middleware protects all `/dashboard`, `/scan`, `/history`, `/profile` routes

### 🔴 CRITICAL — Change Default Secrets

> [!CAUTION]
> The current `.env.local` has hardcoded secrets. NEVER use these in production!

| Secret | Current (INSECURE) | Action |
|--------|-------------------|--------|
| `ADMIN_PASSWORD` | `Norla@Admin2026` | Change to something unique |
| `ADMIN_JWT_SECRET` | `norla-admin-secret-key-change-in-production-2026` | Generate random: `node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"` |
| Session HMAC key | Falls back to `ADMIN_JWT_SECRET` | Same as above — will be secure once JWT secret is changed |

### 🔴 CRITICAL — Remove Dev OTP Code Exposure

Currently in `src/app/api/otp/send/route.ts`, dev mode returns OTP in response:
```typescript
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development') {
  return NextResponse.json({ dev_code: code }); // ← Safe, NODE_ENV=production on Render
}
```
✅ This is already safe — `NODE_ENV=production` on Render means this branch never executes. No action needed.

### 🔴 CRITICAL — Verify OTP Code Not Leaked in Production Logs

Check `console.log` in OTP verify route — ensure the OTP code itself is not logged in production. Currently:
```typescript
console.log(`[OTP DEV] ${formatted}: ${code}`); // Only in dev branch ✅
```
✅ Safe — only in `process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development'` block.

### 🟡 IMPORTANT — Add `SESSION_SECRET` Env Variable

The session HMAC currently uses `ADMIN_JWT_SECRET` as fallback. Better to have a dedicated secret:

Add to Render env vars:
```
SESSION_SECRET=<generate-32-byte-hex>
```
Then update `src/lib/session.ts` line 13:
```typescript
const SECRET = process.env.SESSION_SECRET || process.env.ADMIN_JWT_SECRET || 'fallback';
```

