### ✅ DONE — Schema & RLS
- Tables: `users`, `otp_codes`, `scans`, `activity_log`, `gemini_api_keys`
- Account deletion API exists (Play Store requirement)

### 🔴 CRITICAL — Run Supabase Migrations

You have migration files but need to verify they're applied:

```sql
-- Check if tables exist in your Supabase dashboard → SQL Editor
SELECT table_name FROM information_schema.tables 
WHERE table_schema = 'public';
```

Required tables:
- [x] `users` — phone, name, dob, sex
- [x] `otp_codes` — phone, code, expires_at  
- [x] `scans` — scan results
- [x] `activity_log` — usage tracking
- [ ] `gemini_api_keys` — if using DB-based keys (currently file-based, OK)

### 🔴 CRITICAL — Enable Row Level Security (RLS)

```sql
-- In Supabase dashboard → SQL Editor
ALTER TABLE users ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE scans ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE otp_codes ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE activity_log ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Service role key bypasses RLS (used by server)
-- Anon key has NO access (as intended)
```

